name: UIImagePickerController.InfoKey
desc: Keys you use to retrieve information from the editing dictionary about the media that the user selected.

items.name: static let cropRect: UIImagePickerController.InfoKey
items.desc: The cropping rectangle that was applied to the original image.

items.name: static let editedImage: UIImagePickerController.InfoKey
items.desc: An image edited by the user.

items.name: static let imageURL: UIImagePickerController.InfoKey
items.desc: The URL of the image file.

items.name: static let livePhoto: UIImagePickerController.InfoKey
items.desc: The Live Photo representation of the selected or captured photo.

items.name: static let mediaType: UIImagePickerController.InfoKey
items.desc: The media type selected by the user.

items.name: static let mediaURL: UIImagePickerController.InfoKey
items.desc: The filesystem URL for the movie.

items.name: static let originalImage: UIImagePickerController.InfoKey
items.desc: The original, uncropped image selected by the user.

items.name: init(rawValue: String)
items.desc: Creates a new editing information key with the specified raw value.
